 to convey the disorienting effect and elusive character of trauma. Informing the work of a number of contemporary artists—including Tacita Dean, Jasper Johns, Mary Kelly, Gabriel Orozco, and Gerhard Richter—the concept of the trace is shown to be vital for any account of the aesthetics of trauma; it has left an indelible mark on the history of photography and art as a whole.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPhotography - Social aspects. 0aPhotographyxSocial aspects. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aanalogue.  achance.  adigitization.  aexposure.  aindexicality.  aphotography.  atrace.  atrauma.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107119360 cprintz978022637002640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226370330423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226370330/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles